The '''Great Rift''' was an astrographic feature of [[The galaxy/Legends|the galaxy]]. It formed one of the borders of the [[Outer Rim Territories/Legends|Outlands]] along with the [[celestial equator]].

The Rebel stronghold at [[Yavin 4/Legends|Yavin 4]] was located in the Great Rift, and apparently [[Utapau (Kessil system)|Utapau]] as well. Yavin 4 was also located in the [[Forbidden Systems]].

==Behind the scenes==
The Great Rift featured in the opening crawl in the first three drafts of the [[Star Wars: Episode IV A New Hope|original film]]. In the third draft, the "Rebel strongholds" are located there, and the [[Imperial Navy/Legends|Imperial starfleet]] reaches Utapau&mdash;what would become [[Tatooine/Legends|Tatooine]]&mdash;as it advances toward them. It was deleted in the fourth draft. The first draft dropped the term Forbidden Systems, and re-characterized Yavin 4 as a Rebel base, thus essentially replacing the Systems with the Rift.

